@node "Usage" "Usage"
@prev "Contents"
@next "Installation"

 UMSFix N=NAME, P=PASSWORD, S=SERVER, SUBSCRIBE/S

 N=NAME             - Name of the user Areafix, normally "Areafix" or "Allfix".
                      Default: "Areafix"
 P=PASSWORD         - Password to login.
                      Default: ""
 S=SERVER           - Your MsgBase.
                      Default: "default"
 SUBSCRIBE/S        - Subscribe and Desubscribe areas from your uplinks.
                      Default: don't subscribe...

@endnode
@node "Installation" "Installation"
@prev "Usage"
@next "History"

 First you have to add a sysop with the name your Groupfix shall have:

( Sysop
    ( Alias
    )
    ( READACCESS "~(#?)" )
    ( WRITEACCESS "~(#?)" )
    ( NETACCESS "#?" )
    ( IMPORT % )
    ( Name Areafix )
    ( Password  )
    ( expire.private 25 )           /* not really needed */
 )

Add...

... "@{"groupfix.password" link "groupfix.password" 0}" for every user with access to the areafix.
... "@{"groupfix.subscribe" link "groupfix.subscribe" 0}" for every user with access to the areafix except for
    those operating in "pass-trough"-mode.
... "@{"groupfix.users" link "groupfix.users" 0}" global.
... "@{"groupfix.remote" link "groupfix.remote" 0}" global.
... "@{"groupfix.groupsvar" link "groupfix.groupsvar" 0}" for users and exporters.

The following are not so important, but very usefull:

... "@{"groupfix.autoexpire" link "groupfix.autoexpire" 0}" global.
... "@{"groupfix.arccmd.<arctype>" link "groupfix.arccmd" 0}" global for every <arctype>.
... "@{"groupfix.forwarddelay" link "groupfix.forwarddelay" 0}" global.
... "@{"groupfix.logfile" link "groupfix.logfile" 0}" global.
... "@{"groupfix.loglevel" link "groupfix.loglevel" 0}" global.
... "@{"groupfix.reportlevel" link "groupfix.reportlevel" 0}" global.
... "@{"groupfix.groupfixname" link "groupfix.groupfixname" 0}" global.

... "@{"groupfix.help" link "groupfix.help" 0}" naming the file send as answer to the "%HELP"-request.
... "@{"groupfix.noaccess" link "groupfix.noaccess" 0}" naming the file send if the user has no access to
    your areafix. E.g. if he does not exist as an exporter in your config.
... "@{"groupfix.pwfailure" link "groupfix.pwfailure" 0}" naming the file send on a password failure.

... "@{"groupfix.groups.<netname>" link "groupfix.groups.netname" 0}" naming the file send as answer to the
    "%LIST"-request.
... "@{"groupfix.groups.local" link "groupfix.groups.local" 0}" naming the file send to local users as answer to the
    "%LIST"-request.
@endnode
@node "History" "History"
@prev "Installation"
@next "Bugs"

 V0.5> (10.02.95)

  - first beta release

 V0.6> (24.02.95)

  - fixed login bug.
  - added @{"groupfix.groupsvar" link "groupfix.groupsvar" 0}.
